76561198057880801,Recommended,296770,15248877,"Posted: 7 April, 2015",all,Religious Nihilist,"TL;DR VERSION: It's short and there's not a lot of variety. It's like someone having the right idea on how to make a cake and was on the right track until they f'd up the mix or burnt it. - Get it when it's on sale if you got about 4 hours to spend.I quite like the controls and the graphics are good enough but I do feel that a lot of stuff was missing considering it's a boxing game with the title """"""REAL"""" Boxing"" because there's really not a lot to this other than ""Fight five times. Do your strength, stamina and speed training. Buy some strength, speed or stamina"" rinse and repeat.WEIGHT DIVISIONS ARE MISSING:My first problem with the game is that there's no weight classes so i'm just assuming because a lot of punching is power punching, all it of it is Heavyweight. Weight divisions can change the game because you can be with the sluggish but powerful Heavyweights or be a light footed, fast moving Flyweight but no, you're just left to a one weight class set.TRAINING:This actually did annoy me a bit because they were on the right track and I really liked the training mini-games but you've only got threeStrength, speed and stamina.It's like ""come on, have some variety guys"" Endurance, practice moves to improve them.IT'S A NO-BRAINER:Go in and box, that's all your career is. Where's the management? There's no schedule and you don't really do anything in your career. Fight 8 times, have a championship match and ""oh, do you want this one deal? yes/no?"" and whatever you choose, it really doesn't have an effect on anything you do or have done; one choice gives you money, the other doesn't.I would have like to have seen an injury system so you have to be careful booking fights and being IN fights otherwise it can end your career early. A schedule calendar where you can book fights, manage signings for a new brand of boxing gear, attending a sport convention, accepting or declining movie/tv deals which effects your career time and a reputation meter so say you can choose to slag someone off on social media and that will get you bad rep or have post-fight decisions like ""shake his hand"" or ""talk trash"" which can lead you to being a good sport or a prick everyone boos at. Now I know that's being REALLY nit-picky because even big combat sport video games like Fight Night and UFC don't have a rep meter but with something called ""Real Boxing"" it would have been nice to see.CUSTOMIZATION:You can’t even change the name of your fighter. The hell? Your choice of boxing gear is very limited and because credits can be used on training you’re most likely to forget it exists because each item is like 500 credits so you’d rather spend it on training. To cut long story short: It doesn’t have create a fighter on it and also you can’t even edit the gear.So all I can say from this is: “It’s nice for it being a short game but the title was too bold a statement and there wasn’t much in the game so you’re best just getting it on sale when it’s like £1-£2.something”"
