76561198088717631,Recommended,296770,13414030,"Posted: 17 December, 2014",all,GameOverDeo,"If you have played previous AAA boxing games, I don't recommend this game for you.If you haven't and want to have a boxing game for your PC, go for it.SCORE: 7/10Real Boxing has the basics of boxing mechanics from jabs, straights, uppers, hooks, clinch, dodge, block and counters. The graphics are great. The character creation is limited which is understandable considering this is not a AAA game. It has a decent career mode and training to impove your stats. It has a shop menu where you can buy items like boxing gloves, shorts and shoes. An excellent feature are the Perks which you can customize depending on your playstyle (e.g. lower stamina drain from hooks)As i said earlier, it has the basic boxing mechanics which makes the gameplay repetitive especially when you're up against tougher opponents which takes a longer time to defeat and having to do the same combo or dodging becomes boring. Because of this you can't develop a deeper and adaptive play style of being an in-fighter, out-fighter or a mixture of both. It could add powered punches (haymakers), step-in/out, side steps, specifics blocks and feints to remedy its limited boxing mechanics. Also the footwork in the game is not smooth and sometimes frustrating."
